				<p><p>If 5V blocks were your only option, then I would say "yes, this is fairly safe" with the caveats:</p>

<ul>
<li>If one cell discharges faster than the other, it will start to deteriorate much faster than the other -- it will last for fewer recharge cycles</li>
<li>You should re-charge them separately, not in series</li>
</ul>

<p>However, if you're looking for an off-the-shelf 10V lithium-ion battery pack, you should consider the 10.8V batteries that are available in many models of cordless drills.  </p>
